<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="154" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d154">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                        <persName type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-28"><hi rend="italic">August 28,
                                        1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>(Mr. Adee directs Mr. Conger to consult General Chaffee with a view
                                to ascertaining, if possible, the fate of Americans at Paoting,
                                reports regarding which are conflicting; and, if any are alive, to
                                report, dating his telegram, if relief can be given.)</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>